import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='lon', y='lat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_capitals = data.groupby('state').count().sort_values(by='city', ascending=False)
    sns.barplot(x=state_capitals.index, y=state_capitals.city, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.axhline(y=state_capitals.city.max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Maximum number of state capitals: {state_capitals.city.max():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # calculate the distance matrix
    coords = data[['lat', 'lon']].values
    dist_matrix = squareform(pdist(coords))

    # create a heatmap of the distance matrix
    sns.heatmap(dist_matrix, cmap='Blues', annot=True, fmt='.1f', xticklabels=data['city'], yticklabels=data['city'])
    plt.title('What is the average distance between state capitals?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
